WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:05.715 --> 00:00:06.716
Enter.

2
00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:14.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

3
00:00:15.934 --> 00:00:18.562
{\an8}Lieutenant Shaw reporting
as ordered. sir.

4
00:00:23.024 --> 00:00:24.276
{\an8}At ease.

5
00:00:29.155 --> 00:00:31.074
{\an8}I believe that's gonna
stick around awhile.

6
00:00:33.034 --> 00:00:36.329
You know. this island is
lousy with sailors. Marines.

7
00:00:37.122 --> 00:00:39.842
You couldn't pick a fight with one
of them instead of two of our own?

8
00:00:42.586 --> 00:00:45.296
{\an8}Sometimes the fight
picks you. sir.

9
00:00:45.297 --> 00:00:46.840
{\an8}What was the fight even about?

10
00:00:50.635 --> 00:00:52.721
{\an8}I guess I just can't
abide bullies. sir.

11
00:00:53.388 --> 00:00:55.473
{\an8}You know. your father threw
a few punches in his day.

12
00:00:56.808 --> 00:00:57.809
Some of them at me.

13
00:00:59.185 --> 00:01:01.062
{\an8}What do you think
he'd make of you now?

14
00:01:03.523 --> 00:01:04.523
<i>I don't know. sir.</i>

15
00:01:05.317 --> 00:01:07.319
{\an8}Maybe we could sober
him up and ask him.

16
00:01:10.572 --> 00:01:11.947
All right.

17
00:01:11.948 --> 00:01:14.034
{\an8}Well. some orders
have come through.

18
00:01:14.618 --> 00:01:17.579
Security escort for
a Japanese scientist.

19
00:01:18.204 --> 00:01:20.164
Sorry. sir. A
Japanese scientist?

20
00:01:20.165 --> 00:01:21.790
This isn't a milk
run. Lieutenant.

21
00:01:21.791 --> 00:01:25.085
We already lost a man on
one of these escort missions

22
00:01:25.086 --> 00:01:26.213
a couple of months back.

23
00:01:27.714 --> 00:01:31.217
{\an8}You will protect. observe. and
report when and if able. Understood?

24
00:01:31.218 --> 00:01:32.468
{\an8}Understood. sir.

25
00:01:32.469 --> 00:01:34.679
Then that is all. Lieutenant.

26
00:01:36.973 --> 00:01:37.974
{\an8}Dismissed.

27
00:01:51.321 --> 00:01:55.367
Excuse me. sir. you don't
happen to be Dr. Miura. would...

28
00:01:57.869 --> 00:01:58.869
Miura?

29
00:02:00.330 --> 00:02:01.331
Sorry.

30
00:02:02.165 --> 00:02:03.333
I think you're here for me.

31
00:02:06.586 --> 00:02:09.004
Wish I could say I was. but
I'm here on army business.

32
00:02:09.506 --> 00:02:11.550
Maybe we can get a drink
on my way out. huh?

33
00:02:13.176 --> 00:02:14.177
Wait a minute.

34
00:02:15.053 --> 00:02:17.263
They told me they were
sending a military escort.

35
00:02:17.264 --> 00:02:19.432
and you're the only
one here in uniform.

36
00:02:24.104 --> 00:02:25.896
I'm supposed to
meet a Dr. Miura.

37
00:02:25.897 --> 00:02:27.147
I'm Keiko Miura.

38
00:02:27.148 --> 00:02:30.276
- You're... Keiko. nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

39
00:02:30.277 --> 00:02:31.361
You must be his daughter?

40
00:02:33.363 --> 00:02:34.488
Or...

41
00:02:34.489 --> 00:02:38.242
I'm sorry. I think there's a little
miscommunication happening here.

42
00:02:38.243 --> 00:02:39.868
- Let's start over.
- Yes. why don't we?

43
00:02:39.869 --> 00:02:41.245
- Okay.
- You are...

44
00:02:41.246 --> 00:02:44.708
I am Lieutenant Leland Lafayette
Shaw III. but you can call me Lee.

45
00:02:46.293 --> 00:02:49.546
I'm Keiko Miura. and you
may call me Dr. Miura.

46
00:02:59.848 --> 00:03:02.183
You know. these things aren't
supposed to go that fast.

47
00:03:05.645 --> 00:03:06.854
Would you like me to drive?

48
00:03:06.855 --> 00:03:07.939
Why?

49
00:03:08.773 --> 00:03:10.191
Am I making you nervous?

50
00:03:11.234 --> 00:03:12.694
Nope. But...

51
00:03:14.154 --> 00:03:16.322
I've been assigned to you
as your military escort.

52
00:03:16.323 --> 00:03:19.950
This is an army jeep and
I'm. you know. the army.

53
00:03:19.951 --> 00:03:22.119
I've been driving up and
down these roads for weeks.

54
00:03:22.120 --> 00:03:23.204
I know the way.

55
00:03:25.790 --> 00:03:26.832
Okay then.

56
00:03:26.833 --> 00:03:29.553
I'm starting to get the feeling you
don't really want me around here.

57
00:03:31.463 --> 00:03:33.464
Aren't you even curious
why you're here?

58
00:03:33.465 --> 00:03:34.549
Very much so.

59
00:03:37.135 --> 00:03:39.345
A WB-29 on a routine
weather mission

60
00:03:39.346 --> 00:03:42.349
scooped up some airborne
radioisotopes over the Philippine Sea.

61
00:03:43.350 --> 00:03:47.144
That's pretty far south for a
Russian bomb test. They don't...

62
00:03:47.145 --> 00:03:49.105
That's because it's
not the Russians.

63
00:03:50.649 --> 00:03:54.235
Well. it's not
us. So. who is it?

64
00:03:54.236 --> 00:03:56.612
Well. they were the wrong
isotopes for bomb fallout.

65
00:03:56.613 --> 00:04:00.658
And meteorological data shows
they likely originated here.

66
00:04:00.659 --> 00:04:01.743
The Philippines?

67
00:04:02.577 --> 00:04:03.617
That's gotta be a mistake.

68
00:04:04.704 --> 00:04:06.039
That's what I'm
here to find out.

69
00:04:07.666 --> 00:04:08.666
Okay.

70
00:04:09.084 --> 00:04:12.045
We should get to work.
Hit the gas. Doc.

71
00:09:18.518 --> 00:09:20.020
Every day the
reading diminishes.

72
00:09:20.562 --> 00:09:23.147
Soon it'll be entirely gone.
and the trail will be lost.

73
00:09:23.148 --> 00:09:25.150
Uh-huh. Got that. Double-time.

74
00:09:25.859 --> 00:09:27.193
Your English is very good.

75
00:09:29.279 --> 00:09:31.990
It came in handy when I did my
postgraduate work at Berkeley.

76
00:09:34.576 --> 00:09:35.619
It's impressive.

77
00:09:36.244 --> 00:09:39.038
But doesn't that make you
a little overqualified

78
00:09:39.039 --> 00:09:40.205
for this snipe hunt?

79
00:09:40.206 --> 00:09:41.707
This what?

80
00:09:41.708 --> 00:09:43.335
Wild-goose chase.

81
00:09:45.754 --> 00:09:48.339
Come on. Doc. Don't you think
if those readings were legit.

82
00:09:48.340 --> 00:09:50.549
Washington would've sent half
the eggheads at Los Alamos

83
00:09:50.550 --> 00:09:51.550
to check it out?

84
00:09:52.052 --> 00:09:54.637
Not a woman. Certainly
not a Japanese woman.

85
00:09:54.638 --> 00:09:56.056
You got that right. Yeah.

86
00:09:58.975 --> 00:10:01.478
You want me to lie and pretend
that's not the way things are?

87
00:10:03.855 --> 00:10:05.856
You're telling me you
didn't take one look at me

88
00:10:05.857 --> 00:10:08.568
and make a snap judgment about
who I am the second we met?

89
00:10:12.280 --> 00:10:15.784
It's not the same. Leland
Lafayette Shaw III.

90
00:10:17.786 --> 00:10:18.954
Suppose it's not.

91
00:10:41.768 --> 00:10:42.769
Do you hear that?

92
00:10:50.068 --> 00:10:51.069
Lieutenant?

93
00:10:58.410 --> 00:10:59.410
Lieutenant?

94
00:11:12.674 --> 00:11:13.675
Hey.

95
00:11:15.427 --> 00:11:16.635
Hey.

96
00:11:16.636 --> 00:11:17.970
Don't move.

97
00:11:17.971 --> 00:11:18.889
Lieutenant.

98
00:11:18.890 --> 00:11:20.389
- Who are you? Who are you?
- Don't shoot.

99
00:11:20.390 --> 00:11:22.558
I'm American. Navy vet.

100
00:11:22.559 --> 00:11:25.604
And what are you doing here. American
Navy vet. huh? You filming us?

101
00:11:26.730 --> 00:11:28.188
Why? You guys doing
something film worthy?

102
00:11:28.189 --> 00:11:30.482
- I asked you a question.
- I'm just asking a question back.

103
00:11:30.483 --> 00:11:31.734
Well. I got the gun. swab.

104
00:11:31.735 --> 00:11:33.235
so who are you and what
are you doing here?

105
00:11:33.236 --> 00:11:35.238
- Lieutenant.
- My name's William Randa.

106
00:11:36.823 --> 00:11:39.784
Okay. Lieutenant Shaw?

107
00:11:41.494 --> 00:11:45.457
Look. I promise I won't shoot
you if you don't shoot me.

108
00:11:46.124 --> 00:11:47.125
Deal?

109
00:11:55.467 --> 00:11:56.467
All right.

110
00:11:56.468 --> 00:11:57.552
All right?

111
00:11:58.762 --> 00:12:01.122
Still haven't answered my
question. What are you doing here?

112
00:12:02.307 --> 00:12:07.228
Well. you could say I'm
on a hunting expedition.

113
00:12:07.229 --> 00:12:09.063
I'm a cryptozoologist.

114
00:12:09.064 --> 00:12:13.026
- You're a cryptozoo... What?
- He studies animals that don't exist.

115
00:12:13.610 --> 00:12:14.611
Yeah.

116
00:12:16.488 --> 00:12:18.782
Atmospheric sampler?
Spectrometer?

117
00:12:19.366 --> 00:12:21.200
- Hey. is this a radiation monitor here?
- Hey.

118
00:12:21.201 --> 00:12:22.618
- Easy.
- Don't touch that.

119
00:12:22.619 --> 00:12:24.454
Sorry. I just... I've
never seen one before.

120
00:12:26.081 --> 00:12:27.456
Just wanted to check it out.

121
00:12:27.457 --> 00:12:30.752
'Cause it seems like maybe we're
out here hunting for the same thing.

122
00:12:32.128 --> 00:12:33.922
And what's that. Mr. Randa?

123
00:12:35.298 --> 00:12:36.424
The truth.

124
00:13:18.091 --> 00:13:19.717
<i>Catey. where have you been?</i>

125
00:13:19.718 --> 00:13:20.718
I'm sorry. I...

126
00:13:20.719 --> 00:13:22.303
<i>I've been calling
and calling you.</i>

127
00:13:22.304 --> 00:13:24.096
Mom. I'm fine. I'm coming home.

128
00:13:24.097 --> 00:13:26.849
<i>Already? What did you find out?</i>

129
00:13:26.850 --> 00:13:28.559
It doesn't have
anything to do with us.

130
00:13:28.560 --> 00:13:30.811
<i>What does that mean? What
does it have to do...</i>

131
00:13:30.812 --> 00:13:32.689
What did it always have
to do with. Mom? Him.

132
00:13:33.231 --> 00:13:34.273
<i>Catey.</i>

133
00:13:34.274 --> 00:13:36.275
- We'll talk when I get home. okay?
- <i>Don't do this.</i>

134
00:13:36.276 --> 00:13:37.777
- Love you. Bye.
- <i>Catey. do not...</i>

135
00:13:44.659 --> 00:13:45.660
American?

136
00:13:47.579 --> 00:13:48.787
Excuse me?

137
00:13:48.788 --> 00:13:50.706
Sorry. I didn't mean
to eavesdrop. I just...

138
00:13:50.707 --> 00:13:52.208
I overheard your accent.

139
00:13:53.251 --> 00:13:56.587
Sometimes this place can make you feel
like you're stranded on another planet.

140
00:13:56.588 --> 00:13:57.672
Glad I could help.

141
00:14:05.472 --> 00:14:07.348
- Where are you heading?
- Look. I don't mean to be rude.

142
00:14:07.349 --> 00:14:10.351
but I've made all the new friends
I can handle for one day. thanks.

143
00:14:10.352 --> 00:14:12.228
Yeah. Nah. nah. Hey.
I totally get it.

144
00:14:12.229 --> 00:14:16.523
This young woman abroad
runs into a strange man

145
00:14:16.524 --> 00:14:17.609
at the train station.

146
00:14:18.610 --> 00:14:21.488
And next thing you know. you're
buried alive in a coffin somewhere.

147
00:14:24.032 --> 00:14:25.867
I can't imagine
that that helped.

148
00:14:27.035 --> 00:14:29.663
Hey. Wait. Look.
Hey. I'm harmless.

149
00:14:30.538 --> 00:14:31.538
My name's Tim.

150
00:14:32.499 --> 00:14:34.541
They don't come much more
harmless than the "Tim" variety.

151
00:14:34.542 --> 00:14:35.627
Have a nice night. Tim.

152
00:14:37.128 --> 00:14:38.672
I need to talk to
you about the files.

153
00:14:40.757 --> 00:14:41.758
I don't...

154
00:14:43.468 --> 00:14:44.468
What files?

155
00:14:44.469 --> 00:14:46.221
I work for Monarch.

156
00:14:49.057 --> 00:14:50.141
You're not in trouble.

157
00:14:50.934 --> 00:14:52.434
Not yet.

158
00:14:52.435 --> 00:14:54.688
Those files belong to us.

159
00:14:55.647 --> 00:14:58.149
and they are more important
than you could possibly imagine.

160
00:15:01.987 --> 00:15:03.154
I need to make a call.

161
00:15:04.864 --> 00:15:07.284
Okay. Let's make a call.

162
00:15:25.218 --> 00:15:26.469
All right. All right.

163
00:15:27.304 --> 00:15:28.555
Make your call.

164
00:15:30.307 --> 00:15:31.308
Speaker. please.

165
00:15:32.809 --> 00:15:33.894
Sure.

166
00:15:35.353 --> 00:15:37.814
<i>Cate? Hello? Cate?</i>

167
00:15:43.778 --> 00:15:45.030
No.

168
00:15:45.864 --> 00:15:46.948
No.

169
00:15:50.660 --> 00:15:52.536
I said you weren't in trouble.

170
00:15:52.537 --> 00:15:54.414
"Yet". You said "yet."

171
00:16:03.882 --> 00:16:05.841
Look. I swear we're
not gonna hurt you.

172
00:16:05.842 --> 00:16:07.009
No. you can't do this.

173
00:16:07.010 --> 00:16:09.470
- I can't let you see where we're going.
- No! You don't understand.

174
00:16:09.471 --> 00:16:11.306
I can't breathe. I can't...

175
00:16:14.059 --> 00:16:14.935
I can't...

176
00:16:14.936 --> 00:16:17.854
Relax. You're gonna be
fine. Just breathe. okay?

177
00:16:18.563 --> 00:16:20.898
- Let me out. Let me out!
- Calm down. Relax.

178
00:16:20.899 --> 00:16:23.693
- Let me out!
- Relax. Calm down.

179
00:16:25.487 --> 00:16:26.571
Hey!

180
00:16:27.489 --> 00:16:29.531
Get her under control. man.

181
00:16:29.532 --> 00:16:30.575
Let me out!

182
00:17:27.924 --> 00:17:28.924
What?

183
00:17:29.509 --> 00:17:30.886
Why aren't you
answering my texts?

184
00:17:31.386 --> 00:17:33.597
When's the last time I
answered one of your texts?

185
00:17:34.264 --> 00:17:36.181
I don't know... I thought...

186
00:17:36.182 --> 00:17:37.266
You thought?

187
00:17:37.267 --> 00:17:39.518
You thought that because
of your crazy family drama

188
00:17:39.519 --> 00:17:42.397
that what happened between
us is ancient history?

189
00:17:44.482 --> 00:17:46.067
What do you want from me?

190
00:17:50.113 --> 00:17:52.407
I found this in my
father's office.

191
00:17:53.742 --> 00:17:55.619
I do audio. not home movies.

192
00:17:58.496 --> 00:18:00.123
I told you I was sorry.

193
00:18:01.124 --> 00:18:02.334
Apology accepted.

194
00:18:03.209 --> 00:18:04.209
I'm sorry too.

195
00:18:05.128 --> 00:18:08.297
I grabbed onto you to
keep my head above water.

196
00:18:08.298 --> 00:18:09.925
and you didn't wanna
drown. I get it.

197
00:18:15.096 --> 00:18:16.097
You should go home now.

198
00:18:16.681 --> 00:18:17.973
Wait. wait. wait.

199
00:18:17.974 --> 00:18:20.559
I want those old
computer files we found.

200
00:18:20.560 --> 00:18:21.727
Why?

201
00:18:21.728 --> 00:18:24.855
Because they're mine. What
difference does it make to you?

202
00:18:24.856 --> 00:18:26.107
I'm busy.

203
00:18:26.900 --> 00:18:28.026
Come back tomorrow.

204
00:19:04.771 --> 00:19:06.565
She sounded French.

205
00:19:07.482 --> 00:19:10.109
You said they were American.

206
00:19:10.110 --> 00:19:11.194
The man was.

207
00:19:13.238 --> 00:19:14.239
Tim?

208
00:19:15.740 --> 00:19:17.909
Do you have some identification?

209
00:19:22.122 --> 00:19:24.457
I lost my bag when I ran away.

210
00:19:25.834 --> 00:19:26.834
My passport...

211
00:19:27.335 --> 00:19:28.753
my phone. all my money.

212
00:19:30.297 --> 00:19:32.591
And you're sure this
wasn't some kind of...

213
00:19:32.883 --> 00:19:34.759
misunderstanding?

214
00:19:36.344 --> 00:19:37.344
What?

215
00:19:38.179 --> 00:19:41.683
Tourists come here to enjoy
what Tokyo has to offer.

216
00:19:43.018 --> 00:19:45.270
The nightlife. Some karaoke.

217
00:19:45.729 --> 00:19:46.771
But...

218
00:19:47.022 --> 00:19:48.440
it's easy to overindulge.

219
00:19:49.608 --> 00:19:51.484
You think I'm drunk?

220
00:19:53.111 --> 00:19:55.322
I was almost kidnapped!

221
00:20:01.411 --> 00:20:03.955
If you feel you are in danger...

222
00:20:05.123 --> 00:20:08.251
I would recommend you
contact the American Embassy.

223
00:20:09.669 --> 00:20:11.046
Wait here.

224
00:20:11.504 --> 00:20:13.048
I will get you the address.

225
00:20:42.077 --> 00:20:43.077
I'm home.

226
00:20:43.286 --> 00:20:44.287
Welcome back.

227
00:20:53.755 --> 00:20:55.006
Have you had dinner?

228
00:20:55.715 --> 00:20:56.715
I'm not hungry.

229
00:20:56.716 --> 00:20:57.634
You haven't?

230
00:20:57.635 --> 00:20:59.177
I was going to
warm up the curry.

231
00:21:00.554 --> 00:21:01.554
What's this?

232
00:21:02.430 --> 00:21:05.141
His life was not easy. you know.

233
00:21:05.850 --> 00:21:08.812
He lost so much
when he was young.

234
00:21:11.690 --> 00:21:13.733
You're defending him?

235
00:21:14.484 --> 00:21:15.569
Aren't you angry?

236
00:21:16.820 --> 00:21:19.823
You're angry. Kentaro.

237
00:21:20.865 --> 00:21:23.243
Do you feel better?

238
00:21:34.379 --> 00:21:36.006
What are you doing?

239
00:21:37.257 --> 00:21:38.300
Now I'm angry too.

240
00:21:40.635 --> 00:21:41.928
Join me. Kentaro.

241
00:21:45.682 --> 00:21:46.682
Seriously?!

242
00:21:46.975 --> 00:21:47.976
Throw it!

243
00:21:50.812 --> 00:21:51.646
More.

244
00:21:51.647 --> 00:21:52.772
Here.

245
00:22:01.239 --> 00:22:03.325
Now we both feel better. right?

246
00:22:05.493 --> 00:22:06.870
A little.

247
00:22:10.749 --> 00:22:12.417
I'll warm up the curry.

248
00:22:34.981 --> 00:22:37.650
So. you guys are following
the radiation. aren't you?

249
00:22:37.651 --> 00:22:38.776
And how do you know about that?

250
00:22:38.777 --> 00:22:41.028
Well. I know you're not
gonna find what's out there

251
00:22:41.029 --> 00:22:42.488
following a Geiger counter.

252
00:22:42.489 --> 00:22:44.406
What should we be
following. Mr. Randa?

253
00:22:44.407 --> 00:22:45.909
Just Billy.

254
00:22:46.660 --> 00:22:49.370
I think you should be following
the stories. Folklore. Legends.

255
00:22:49.371 --> 00:22:52.790
You know. the people of these
mountains. they have an oral tradition

256
00:22:52.791 --> 00:22:56.378
about a dragon that carves a
path of fire across the sky.

257
00:22:57.796 --> 00:23:00.465
Or maybe a path of
ionizing radiation.

258
00:23:02.008 --> 00:23:05.387
So. you're hunting dragons.

259
00:23:06.930 --> 00:23:08.973
I told you. I'm
looking for the truth.

260
00:23:08.974 --> 00:23:10.975
That's great. But
we got work to do.

261
00:23:10.976 --> 00:23:12.726
so it's time for you
to hit the trail. bud.

262
00:23:12.727 --> 00:23:14.228
Wait a minute. Lieutenant.

263
00:23:14.229 --> 00:23:16.773
I don't think it's such a bad
idea for Mr. Randa to join us.

264
00:23:17.732 --> 00:23:19.025
I think it's a terrible idea.

265
00:23:19.609 --> 00:23:21.569
You're not here to think
for me. Lieutenant.

266
00:23:21.570 --> 00:23:24.029
Look at him. Smell him.

267
00:23:24.030 --> 00:23:25.656
He's probably been lost
out here for weeks.

268
00:23:25.657 --> 00:23:27.283
Hey. hey. I know
exactly where I am. pal.

269
00:23:27.284 --> 00:23:28.659
- Do you?
- Yes.

270
00:23:28.660 --> 00:23:32.037
No. Look. I am here at the behest
of the US Army. and my orders are...

271
00:23:32.038 --> 00:23:34.456
Your orders are to provide me with
whatever assistance I require.

272
00:23:34.457 --> 00:23:38.168
My orders are to provide you
with operational security.

273
00:23:38.169 --> 00:23:42.590
and I cannot do that with our new friend.
Billy the jungle hermit. hanging around.

274
00:23:42.591 --> 00:23:43.675
Wow.

275
00:23:47.095 --> 00:23:49.306
Fine. Just go then.

276
00:23:50.515 --> 00:23:51.515
Don't tempt me. Doc.

277
00:23:53.059 --> 00:23:54.268
I didn't ask for you.

278
00:23:54.269 --> 00:23:57.062
I don't need you and
I don't want you.

279
00:23:57.063 --> 00:24:00.942
So. you are relieved of
any responsibility for me.

280
00:24:02.819 --> 00:24:03.987
Dismissed.

281
00:24:07.282 --> 00:24:08.825
I'll send someone
back with the jeep.

282
00:24:21.129 --> 00:24:22.255
Shall we go?

283
00:24:36.436 --> 00:24:38.687
So. have you ever seen a dragon?

284
00:24:38.688 --> 00:24:39.731
Once.

285
00:24:40.232 --> 00:24:43.025
Well. maybe. It's kind of
why I started doing this.

286
00:24:43.026 --> 00:24:44.777
Trying to prove I'm not crazy.

287
00:24:44.778 --> 00:24:46.153
You think I'm crazy?

288
00:24:46.154 --> 00:24:47.572
I don't even know you.

289
00:24:48.073 --> 00:24:49.074
That's true.

290
00:24:49.574 --> 00:24:51.454
Do you often follow strange
men into the jungle?

291
00:24:52.410 --> 00:24:54.412
This is my second time today.

292
00:24:57.165 --> 00:24:58.416
We call 'em MUTO's.

293
00:24:59.251 --> 00:25:02.503
For Massive Unidentified
Terrestrial Organisms.

294
00:25:02.504 --> 00:25:04.004
I came up with that.

295
00:25:04.005 --> 00:25:07.675
Terrestrial. So. you don't
think they're space aliens?

296
00:25:07.676 --> 00:25:09.219
You do think I'm crazy.

297
00:25:09.886 --> 00:25:10.720
I'm a scientist.

298
00:25:10.721 --> 00:25:12.930
I believe what the evidence
tells me to be true.

299
00:25:12.931 --> 00:25:14.140
Okay.

300
00:25:15.141 --> 00:25:18.143
Everyone around here tells
some version of the same story.

301
00:25:18.144 --> 00:25:19.813
- Okay.
- Lights in the sky.

302
00:25:21.439 --> 00:25:24.400
And whatever's making them
has been tracing the same path

303
00:25:24.401 --> 00:25:28.028
over and over and over
again. going back centuries.

304
00:25:28.029 --> 00:25:31.032
- Like comets.
- No. More like migrating birds.

305
00:25:31.950 --> 00:25:32.951
Hold on.

306
00:25:34.035 --> 00:25:35.495
I have to show you something.

307
00:25:36.788 --> 00:25:38.706
These are the tracks

308
00:25:38.707 --> 00:25:41.418
of the radiation readings from
our surveillance aircraft.

309
00:25:46.798 --> 00:25:47.924
See this?

310
00:25:55.557 --> 00:25:56.933
Incredible.

311
00:26:00.228 --> 00:26:01.813
- This way. This way. Come on.
- Okay.

312
00:26:02.522 --> 00:26:03.647
Where are we going?

313
00:26:03.648 --> 00:26:05.233
We're following the map.

314
00:26:18.079 --> 00:26:19.122
We're almost there.

315
00:26:19.789 --> 00:26:21.333
Almost where?

316
00:26:24.628 --> 00:26:25.712
What is it?

317
00:26:31.301 --> 00:26:32.469
What is that?

318
00:26:38.016 --> 00:26:39.017
The <i>Lawton.</i>

319
00:27:20.225 --> 00:27:21.226
I don't know.

320
00:27:22.310 --> 00:27:23.894
You wanna take a look
and see what's on these.

321
00:27:23.895 --> 00:27:25.730
I have no idea if
they're any good but...

322
00:27:33.530 --> 00:27:34.531
You do it.

323
00:27:51.006 --> 00:27:55.218
Hiroshi was eighteen when
his father died in Vietnam.

324
00:27:59.264 --> 00:28:02.392
His Uncle Lee was the
only family he had left.

325
00:28:03.310 --> 00:28:06.313
If they were so close. why
didn't Dad ever mention him?

326
00:28:08.315 --> 00:28:10.066
I think something
happened between them.

327
00:28:11.026 --> 00:28:12.569
He didn't like to talk about

328
00:28:13.320 --> 00:28:15.864
some parts of his life.

329
00:28:17.991 --> 00:28:19.367
Is he still alive?

330
00:28:20.952 --> 00:28:22.037
Oh. I don't know.

331
00:28:23.538 --> 00:28:25.498
This would have been
a long time ago.

332
00:28:28.209 --> 00:28:29.336
Sorry.

333
00:28:31.338 --> 00:28:32.756
"CALL ME! IT'S IMPORTANT!"

334
00:28:36.718 --> 00:28:37.843
I'll get it.

335
00:28:37.844 --> 00:28:38.887
Thank you.

336
00:28:47.229 --> 00:28:48.229
Good Evening.

337
00:28:48.647 --> 00:28:50.231
Do you speak English?

338
00:28:50.232 --> 00:28:51.650
Yes.

339
00:28:52.192 --> 00:28:53.943
That's great. actually.

340
00:28:53.944 --> 00:28:57.112
That makes this much
easier. for me anyway.

341
00:28:57.113 --> 00:28:58.197
May we come in?

342
00:28:58.198 --> 00:29:01.075
- No. Who are you?
- It's official business.

343
00:29:01.076 --> 00:29:03.869
We're with a special
government task force.

344
00:29:03.870 --> 00:29:05.788
- Which government?
- You know what?

345
00:29:05.789 --> 00:29:08.499
We'll be in and out
before you even know it.

346
00:29:08.500 --> 00:29:10.961
Wow. You have a lovely home.

347
00:29:11.753 --> 00:29:13.088
Who are they?

348
00:29:14.673 --> 00:29:16.174
What do you want?

349
00:29:17.634 --> 00:29:19.093
I want Bill Randa's files.

350
00:29:19.094 --> 00:29:20.386
No. you need to leave.

351
00:29:20.387 --> 00:29:22.805
No. you need to hand
over those files.

352
00:29:22.806 --> 00:29:25.891
Otherwise. you. your friends.

353
00:29:25.892 --> 00:29:28.228
and your mother are gonna
be in a lot of trouble.

354
00:29:28.603 --> 00:29:29.479
Kentaro...?

355
00:29:29.479 --> 00:29:30.479
It's okay.

356
00:29:30.981 --> 00:29:33.650
There's something
that your son stole.

357
00:29:35.235 --> 00:29:37.195
He's going to have
to come with us.

358
00:29:39.114 --> 00:29:40.114
Is it true?

359
00:29:40.282 --> 00:29:42.116
Did you take
something of theirs?

360
00:29:42.117 --> 00:29:43.576
They say I stole some files.

361
00:29:43.577 --> 00:29:44.786
Enough.

362
00:29:45.036 --> 00:29:46.413
Let's have it.

363
00:29:47.163 --> 00:29:52.127
If he returns whatever he
took. will you leave him alone?

364
00:29:52.711 --> 00:29:53.711
Of course.

365
00:29:58.550 --> 00:30:00.343
If you have what they
are looking for...

366
00:30:01.052 --> 00:30:02.512
you should give it to them.

367
00:30:03.179 --> 00:30:04.222
Are you sure?

368
00:30:06.933 --> 00:30:09.603
It must be very important.

369
00:30:15.275 --> 00:30:16.276
I'll get it.

370
00:30:17.736 --> 00:30:19.321
Amazing. Thank you.

371
00:30:20.572 --> 00:30:23.074
Tea? You like tea?

372
00:30:24.075 --> 00:30:25.075
Tea?

373
00:30:25.493 --> 00:30:26.827
No. We're good. Thanks.

374
00:30:26.828 --> 00:30:29.247
I hope my son hasn't
caused any trouble for you.

375
00:30:29.873 --> 00:30:31.373
He's a good man now.

376
00:30:31.374 --> 00:30:34.002
but when he was younger
there were so many problems!

377
00:30:34.711 --> 00:30:36.587
- So much drinking!
- Hurry up!

378
00:30:36.588 --> 00:30:39.174
I wanted him to
find a nice girl.

379
00:30:39.883 --> 00:30:41.676
Someone to settle him down.

380
00:30:42.260 --> 00:30:44.261
You are very attractive.

381
00:30:44.262 --> 00:30:45.597
Are you single?

382
00:30:49.476 --> 00:30:51.352
Oh. shit.

383
00:30:51.353 --> 00:30:53.688
- Shit.
- Kentaro!

384
00:30:54.773 --> 00:30:55.773
Open up!

385
00:30:55.857 --> 00:30:57.400
Kentaro. run!

386
00:31:46.533 --> 00:31:47.866
You know this ship?

387
00:31:47.867 --> 00:31:49.286
USS <i>Lawton.</i>

388
00:31:50.245 --> 00:31:53.498
Went down 200 miles
west of Pearl in 1943.

389
00:31:54.124 --> 00:31:55.500
Pearl Harbor?

390
00:31:56.293 --> 00:31:58.669
That's 5.000 miles from here.

391
00:31:58.670 --> 00:31:59.754
Exactly.

392
00:32:17.439 --> 00:32:18.607
Is this safe?

393
00:32:29.618 --> 00:32:30.785
Mr. Randa.

394
00:32:31.745 --> 00:32:34.788
You said you study
myths. stories.

395
00:32:34.789 --> 00:32:37.667
I'm interested in why people
tell the stories they tell.

396
00:32:42.464 --> 00:32:44.090
What inspired the storyteller.

397
00:32:51.848 --> 00:32:52.849
What terrified 'em.

398
00:33:11.409 --> 00:33:12.410
What is it?

399
00:33:14.829 --> 00:33:17.582
Mr. Randa. Maybe we
should stick together...

400
00:33:32.973 --> 00:33:33.974
Mr. Randa.

401
00:33:36.810 --> 00:33:37.811
Billy.

402
00:33:47.612 --> 00:33:49.155
You were on this ship.

403
00:33:52.867 --> 00:33:53.868
Yeah.

404
00:33:57.289 --> 00:33:58.999
Is this what you
were looking for?

405
00:33:59.666 --> 00:34:01.167
Did you know it was here?

406
00:34:05.130 --> 00:34:06.131
Did I know?

407
00:34:10.969 --> 00:34:12.178
Let's say hoped.

408
00:34:15.181 --> 00:34:16.266
Not very scientific.

409
00:34:19.311 --> 00:34:21.688
I know we hit something
in the water that night.

410
00:34:22.355 --> 00:34:24.024
We figured it was
a Japanese sub.

411
00:34:27.068 --> 00:34:29.153
The whole ship went down
in less than three minutes.

412
00:34:30.822 --> 00:34:31.907
Who else survived?

413
00:34:36.494 --> 00:34:37.495
Only me.

414
00:35:41.601 --> 00:35:42.810
Going to the back.

415
00:35:42.811 --> 00:35:43.895
Okay.

416
00:36:00.245 --> 00:36:01.955
Who are you? Jason Bourne?

417
00:36:03.456 --> 00:36:05.667
You're from San Francisco.
You were there that day.

418
00:36:06.251 --> 00:36:07.459
You don't have a bag packed.

419
00:36:07.460 --> 00:36:09.795
ready to head for higher ground
when the tide starts rising?

420
00:36:09.796 --> 00:36:12.924
Yeah. It's full of bottled water
and batteries. not extra passports.

421
00:36:16.720 --> 00:36:18.305
- May.
- Hey. are you okay?

422
00:36:19.097 --> 00:36:20.639
What is she doing here?

423
00:36:20.640 --> 00:36:22.517
Hey. She's in this too.

424
00:36:24.686 --> 00:36:25.978
Somebody's after those files.

425
00:36:25.979 --> 00:36:27.563
Why don't we just give
'em what they want?

426
00:36:27.564 --> 00:36:29.773
Maybe then they'll
leave all of us alone.

427
00:36:29.774 --> 00:36:31.483
Okay. yeah. Good luck with that.

428
00:36:31.484 --> 00:36:32.818
What's your plan? Just run?

429
00:36:32.819 --> 00:36:35.362
Me? I have contacts. I
can get us fake passports.

430
00:36:35.363 --> 00:36:37.907
I don't want a fake passport.
I want my real passport.

431
00:36:37.908 --> 00:36:39.199
I haven't done anything wrong.

432
00:36:39.200 --> 00:36:41.285
Okay. When have people in
power ever cared about...

433
00:36:41.286 --> 00:36:42.370
Hold on.

434
00:36:44.247 --> 00:36:45.457
I know where to go.

435
00:36:47.250 --> 00:36:48.585
Trust me.

436
00:36:49.753 --> 00:36:50.754
Come on.

437
00:36:58.303 --> 00:37:00.722
- What is that?
- I don't know.

438
00:37:03.225 --> 00:37:05.143
Looks organic.

439
00:37:35.423 --> 00:37:36.424
Oh. God.

440
00:37:41.471 --> 00:37:42.806
There are so many.

441
00:37:47.435 --> 00:37:49.020
When did you say this ship sank?

442
00:37:50.272 --> 00:37:51.481
Nine years ago.

443
00:37:54.234 --> 00:37:56.151
I think I've seen everything
I need to in here.

444
00:37:56.152 --> 00:37:57.404
Yeah.

445
00:38:06.788 --> 00:38:08.038
That wasn't there before.

446
00:38:08.039 --> 00:38:09.833
- This is fresh.
- Fresh what?

447
00:38:10.500 --> 00:38:12.418
We'll find another
way outta here.

448
00:38:12.419 --> 00:38:14.044
How did it get here?

449
00:38:14.045 --> 00:38:15.880
Is there something in
here that's making it...

450
00:38:15.881 --> 00:38:17.257
I don't know. Come on.

451
00:38:37.652 --> 00:38:39.153
You're here to see the Colonel?

452
00:38:39.154 --> 00:38:41.114
Yes. we are.

453
00:38:41.823 --> 00:38:43.491
If he's still alive.

454
00:38:43.867 --> 00:38:45.744
So. we can see the Colonel?

455
00:39:07.724 --> 00:39:09.017
Colonel Shaw?

456
00:39:22.489 --> 00:39:23.490
What's your name?

457
00:39:24.783 --> 00:39:25.784
Kentaro.

458
00:39:26.284 --> 00:39:27.326
Kentaro what?

459
00:39:27.327 --> 00:39:28.411
Randa.

460
00:39:30.580 --> 00:39:34.626
Oh. my God. You're
Hiroshi's boy.

461
00:39:36.461 --> 00:39:37.962
And you?

462
00:39:37.963 --> 00:39:40.507
I'm Cate Randa.

463
00:39:41.216 --> 00:39:42.300
Course you are.

464
00:39:45.387 --> 00:39:48.472
I didn't know Hiroshi
even had a daughter.

465
00:39:48.473 --> 00:39:50.641
Well. I didn't
know he had a son.

466
00:39:50.642 --> 00:39:53.270
Turns out he was good
at keeping secrets.

467
00:39:57.566 --> 00:39:59.234
Not my drama. No relation.

468
00:40:00.151 --> 00:40:02.362
- We wanted to ask you about our fa...
- Why don't we...

469
00:40:05.282 --> 00:40:06.283
Yeah. Come on.

470
00:40:07.492 --> 00:40:08.493
Let's get some air.

471
00:40:09.494 --> 00:40:10.620
Come on.

472
00:40:15.709 --> 00:40:19.044
If you guys could just kinda keep
your voices down. that'd be good.

473
00:40:19.045 --> 00:40:20.630
Tell me. how'd you get here?

474
00:40:21.464 --> 00:40:22.464
Rented a minivan.

475
00:40:22.465 --> 00:40:25.844
That's good. But I mean.
how did you find me?

476
00:40:26.678 --> 00:40:27.678
My mom.

477
00:40:27.679 --> 00:40:29.264
- Emiko.
- Yes.

478
00:40:34.019 --> 00:40:35.603
We found something
in my father's safe.

479
00:40:35.604 --> 00:40:37.313
- Kentaro.
- What? He's my great uncle Lee.

480
00:40:37.314 --> 00:40:39.356
What did you find in the safe?

481
00:40:39.357 --> 00:40:40.733
Old computer files.

482
00:40:40.734 --> 00:40:43.278
Bunch of crazy
shit. Monster shit.

483
00:40:43.778 --> 00:40:47.407
Can you please. please
keep your voices down?

484
00:40:48.700 --> 00:40:51.952
What's this all about? Why are you
here? And you gotta make it kinda quick.

485
00:40:51.953 --> 00:40:54.122
We wanna find out what
happened to my father.

486
00:40:55.248 --> 00:40:56.249
You tell me.

487
00:40:57.542 --> 00:41:00.419
Right after G-Day. he said he
had someplace he needed to go.

488
00:41:00.420 --> 00:41:01.587
Wouldn't tell us where.

489
00:41:01.588 --> 00:41:03.505
but a week later we were
told the plane he was on

490
00:41:03.506 --> 00:41:04.786
disappeared somewhere in Alaska.

491
00:41:05.675 --> 00:41:07.886
Turns out he had a whole
secret life in Japan.

492
00:41:08.929 --> 00:41:10.512
I came here to try
and figure it out.

493
00:41:10.513 --> 00:41:13.015
but now we're being chased by
these Monarch people and...

494
00:41:13.016 --> 00:41:15.976
"Disappeared"? As in. no body?

495
00:41:15.977 --> 00:41:17.562
<i>No death certificate?</i>

496
00:41:18.438 --> 00:41:20.565
- What are you saying?
- Hey.

497
00:41:21.233 --> 00:41:22.609
Hey. what is this place?

498
00:41:23.860 --> 00:41:28.822
This place is what Monarch
euphemistically refers to

499
00:41:28.823 --> 00:41:30.867
as "secure asset management."

500
00:41:32.118 --> 00:41:33.577
Right. So. you're
imprisoned here.

501
00:41:33.578 --> 00:41:35.412
Okay. Well. we're leaving.

502
00:41:35.413 --> 00:41:37.915
Yeah. you can try. but they're
just gonna keep following you

503
00:41:37.916 --> 00:41:41.503
and following you and following you.
until they finally get what they want.

504
00:41:42.003 --> 00:41:43.003
Or?

505
00:41:43.004 --> 00:41:44.381
Well. that's up to you.

506
00:41:44.965 --> 00:41:47.383
Now. you can choke down that
mountain of Monarch bullshit

507
00:41:47.384 --> 00:41:49.886
about your father
disappearing without a trace.

508
00:41:53.515 --> 00:41:56.600
Or we can get the hell
outta here right now

509
00:41:56.601 --> 00:41:58.937
and find out what really
happened with your dad.

510
00:42:03.066 --> 00:42:05.735
Now you got just about 60
seconds to make up your minds.

511
00:42:10.949 --> 00:42:12.158
What's it gonna be?

512
00:42:19.666 --> 00:42:20.708
Here. this way.

513
00:42:20.709 --> 00:42:22.042
Are you sure?

514
00:42:22.043 --> 00:42:24.004
I did two tours in
this tin can. Doc.

515
00:42:28.550 --> 00:42:29.634
What is that?

516
00:42:33.680 --> 00:42:36.349
- Let's keep it moving. Come on.
- Okay.

517
00:42:40.770 --> 00:42:42.938
- Are you all right?
- Oh. Jesus Christ.

518
00:42:42.939 --> 00:42:44.983
- Go back! Go!
- Oh. my God.

519
00:42:49.112 --> 00:42:50.989
- Oh. my God!
- No.

520
00:42:52.324 --> 00:42:53.450
Hang on!

521
